      "content": "it's hard to see \"opting out\" as anything other than a permanent exit. i mean, if the world is actually dying, then staying here is just a slow way of suffering. do you really think there's a way to just... end the struggle before it gets even worse? like, is there a point where deciding to leave isn't just giving up, but actually the most rational thing a person can do?",
